USA Inbound Border Crossing Data

Marc Alexander

2024-07-10

US-Canada Border

The United States and Canada share the world’s longest internation border, which is 5,525 miles long. It spans 13 U.S states and has 84 ports of entry, with 1/3 of the northern border comprised of just the eastern flank of Alaska.

US-Mexico Border

The United States border with Mexico is considerably shorter at 1,954 miles. It covers 4 states with 28 ports of entry. The US-Mexico border is about 1/3 as long, has 1/3 the Ports of Entry, covers 1/4 the number of states, but has 5X more border crossings than the US-Canada border.

In-bound Crossing Volume and Density by Border

The US-Canada Border is 3X longer than the US-Mexico Border and has 3X more ports of entry to cover the distance. In spite of the shorter border, the US-Mexico border has 4X more border crossings than the US-Canada Border.
